The image resembles a Shivalingam covered with sandal paste. It is only once a year, during the<strong>Chandana Visarjana</strong>that the sandal paste is removed, and the image is seen by pilgrims. The main deity is covered with sandal paste(Chandanam) throughout the year except on Vaishaka Sudda Thadiya. On this auspicious day, the main deity givesNijapada Darshan( the true form of God ) for 12hrs only.
